Sitting here with my family on holiday reflecting on the vibration we all felt on NYD that’s often impossible to put into words. 

I received the most beautiful messages this week that perfectly expressed what I always hope to convey through my music. 

“Your music cuts across race, gender, sexuality, age, and class. Everyone is welcome at your parties and I have always felt safe and seen. Creating a space like that is the special sauce that most parties struggle to achieve”

Thank you for bringing your vibes, thank you for sharing your love on the dance-floor. Thank you to everyone that helped create this unified experience. ❤️

I have never publicly honored my brother Cesare since his passing in 2006. I think of him so often. Every time I see a photo or video of myself playing, I see him. Every time I think of him my heart aches as much as it is full.  Fact is, there would never be deejay Victor Calderone without the story of Cesare Calderone.  It is him that I owe so much to. 

He was my truest mentor. He gave me the incredible gift of music when I was just a teenager. He taught me how to deejay. He snuck me into my fist after-hours, the “Fun House” in NYC, and it changed my life forever.  Cesare was an outstanding deejay. He taught me if you’re going to play, play with all the energy in your heart and the people with feel that. His words echo true every time I deejay to this day. 

Cesare struggled with addiction for years, right up until the day I stood beside him, holding his hand, and watched him take his last breath.  I will never forget that poignant moment and the emotions that followed.  I carried so much guilt for feeling like I could have done more during his struggle with his disease. I made peace with it years later knowing there was no clear path to help him at the time and we all struggled together. He was an amazing human — funny, loyal, good hearted and was loved by so many of his friends. 

Today, I celebrate and honor you on your birthday. I know you’re up there so proud of your little brother. I will continue to play with you in my heart. Happy Birthday Chez. I love you and miss you so much. RIP

Legendary New York DJ and producer Victor Calderone has consistently proven himself to be a sonically curious artist. Try fitting him into a particular box and you’ll undoubtedly be doing a disservice to some part of his illustrious career.  Delving into the music industry at the age of 15, Victor became renowned for his club remixes of pop icons like Madonna, Beyoncé, Sting and countless others, while building a reputation for his epic 12-16 hour sets at influential clubs like The Roxy, Pacha, and Crobar just to name a few.  Not one to rest on his laurels, Calderone also approached his passion for techno with the same intensity, eventually earning recognition from legends like Carl Cox and Richie Hawtin for the music he created and produced within this genre.  Nowadays, Victor’s renewed energy and commitment to reviving his MATTER+ imprint allows him to craft music that experiments with progressive sound design. His continued curiosity makes every new release shine, even after 30 years in the game.

The Bullitt Agency is proud to welcome Victor Calderone into the family for Worldwide Representation.

Wow, what a way to kick off 2024.  Life is a series of lessons. For most, a classroom gives way to their education. My schoolhouse was my basement, with my brother, on vinyl. I studied in legendary nightclubs like Paradise Garage and Funhouse when I was 16. This was my education and last night was yet another New York City lesson.

Coming up as a deejay in NYC has instilled a profound reverence in me that has deeply influenced the way I hear and play music. It’s something I can barely give words to, it’s a feeling. And it is etched deep into my soul, shaping a significant part of my identity as an artist. NYC, yesterday was INSANE. 14 hours of seriously sexy old-school New York vibes. A journey for sure and one that we all went on together ❤️🙏🏽 

A massive thank you to the @teksupport crew and to everyone that helped create this amazing journey. 

I hope to always be on the path of discovery. To remain open to the lessons of life and of music…to grow, to absorb, and adapt as an artist while always remaining true to my identity.

ID - Big Fun, @avision remix
